Police in Kitale are investigating the circumstances under which a class six pupil hanged herself. According to Francisca Ingosi, a neighbour, the pupil quarreled with her mother after she suspected that she was in a sexual relationship with a boy. Ingosi said the frequent collision with her mother made her uncomfortable. She said the deceased revealed this in a suicide note she left behind. Ingosi said the girl likely hang herself at around 4 pm during heavy rains when she was alone at home. The body was moved to Kitale Hospital mortuary for postmortem. Related: Standard six pupil commits suicide after being pregnant Read also: Kisii boy, 14, hangs self over poor living conditions  Click here for the latest political news